<br>
I think the game is addictive, but more so than the game itself it is the relationships you build in it.  I've been seriously considering leaving and did leave for a short while. I came back but even though I got some things I wanted for my characters during this time, I've been thinking it's time to find something else to do.  I will play but not with the same zeal and dreams I had about the game.  I've seen the good and the bad in the game, which has little to do with the game itself it's more about the people who play it, they make it good or bad.  <br>
<br>
I like the characters and I like playing &quot;dress up&quot; with them, but interaction with other people is what makes it or breaks it for me.  Sometimes the interactions are great and everything works like a fine tuned machine, other times there's a breakdown. I will seriously cut down my time in EQ, I will do raids and whatever but not going to pursue the end like I did.  I got there and it was anti-climatic.<br>
<br>
If this wasn't a multi player game I'm sure a lot of people wouldn't fight so hard to reach 60. Playing something that becomes increasingly harder and more tedious as a stand alone, vs computer game,  wouldn't keep you hooked as EQ does.<br>
